					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The kiss of death for a two-player hack would be one player taking the wrong path in 4-4; there's no way to work around that without breaking the game rules.  Both players would have to cooperate on every little movement to make the screen scroll properly.  What might be interesting is a PC remake where the playfield stretches between both players ala NSMB Wii, but even that could look funky with the pattern castles, or just take the uncreative way out and do a split-screen ala Sonic 2.</div>

